WEBVTT

00:00.962 --> 00:06.128
The mission of our church is to change our world by developing Christ followers who love God and who love people.

00:06.749 --> 00:15.941
And that we know, according to Matthew 28, Mark 16, Acts chapter 1, we have been called to go into Jerusalem and Judea, Samaria, to the uttermost parts of the earth.

00:15.961 --> 00:20.667
We have been called to go out and to share the gospel of Jesus Christ with others.

00:20.727 --> 00:26.514
We have been called to go into perverbally knock on the doors of people in our communities.

00:26.658 --> 00:28.240
to let them know who Christ is.

00:28.300 --> 00:30.002
And that is what we are doing.

00:30.283 --> 00:34.148
We are simply fulfilling what Christ called the church to do.

00:34.869 --> 00:39.155
And that is a passion, that's a heart that has always been in our church.

00:39.175 --> 00:42.259
In fact, this week I had a conversation with a young lady in our church.

00:42.679 --> 00:46.945
She's not quite that young anymore, but she's youngish in our church today.

00:47.366 --> 00:50.610
And she told me, she said, you know, I remember when I was a little girl,

00:51.042 --> 01:02.214
And I remember I lived over on a certain street in the town, and there was this guy who came and knocked on the door of our house, and he invited our family to come to church, and then he would come back again.

01:02.274 --> 01:11.023
In fact, my mom eventually said that guy's coming back again, and they would send a bus by to pick up the kids, and here's the deal.

01:11.904 --> 01:17.490
That family was impacted, and that young lady was impacted with the gospel, and she's sitting in this church today.

01:18.466 --> 01:25.117
You have no idea the impact that you can have when you simply are willing to offer and to extend an invitation.

01:25.858 --> 01:29.244
And that is exactly what we're going to be talking about today and over the coming weeks.

01:30.165 --> 01:33.551
The invitations that God has called us to give.

01:34.212 --> 01:40.382
And we're going to do that by looking in the scriptures and talking about the invitations that were extended by Christ himself.

01:41.043 --> 01:43.026
Now today we're going to be in John chapter 1.

01:43.394 --> 01:44.596
It's an important passage.

01:44.636 --> 01:46.580
It's a passage obviously in the first part of it.

01:46.600 --> 02:04.050
It talks about in the beginning was the word and we know that was talking about Christ is the the Apostle John the the blood disciples writing speaking of Jesus and then a few verses later he begins talking about the one who came to to proclaim the message of Jesus who would come and talking about John the Baptist.

02:04.162 --> 02:14.280
Then we then read in that passage how John the Baptist was there was approached by many of the religious leaders of the time and they're asking the question are you the one or you the Messiah and he made the statement.

02:14.320 --> 02:15.101
No, it's not me.

02:15.422 --> 02:22.214
I'm here to tell people about that one, but he's going to come and I'm not worthy to even put the straps on his on his sandals.

02:22.254 --> 02:25.760
I'm not even worthy to be in his presence.

02:25.780 --> 02:28.946
And then we walk into the passage in verse 35, we're going to be today.

02:29.666 --> 02:32.409
And we're going to look at seven different invitations.

02:32.469 --> 02:38.076
I guess I should do seven different invitations that are found within the last part of this chapter.

02:38.797 --> 02:45.765
Seven invitations were offered and extended by different individuals, one being Christ, the others that were involved as well.

02:46.425 --> 02:51.311
Invitations that were extended by people who just simply said, come and see.

02:51.351 --> 02:57.458
Just simply say it only, look at this man, Jesus.

02:58.402 --> 03:02.868
And so we're going to look at this passage today, seven invitations that are found within it.

03:03.309 --> 03:05.411
I've broken it down into three different sections here.

03:05.451 --> 03:07.775
The first section, if you're taking notes, is just simply this.

03:08.135 --> 03:09.477
It's the invitation to see.

03:10.418 --> 03:11.800
The invitation to see.

03:11.860 --> 03:14.924
Let's go to John 1 and begin with verse 35.

03:15.465 --> 03:17.027
It says these words.

03:17.067 --> 03:22.174
The next day, again, this is after John the Baptist has been approached by the religious leaders of that day.

03:22.614 --> 03:28.402
He says, the next day, John, John the Baptist, not John the Apostle, John the Baptist was standing with two of his disciples.

03:28.674 --> 03:33.042
And when he saw Jesus passing by, he said, look, the Lamb of God.

03:33.683 --> 03:36.268
The two disciples heard him say this and followed Jesus.

03:36.729 --> 03:40.897
And when Jesus turned to notice them, follow him and then he asked them, well, what are you looking for?

03:40.937 --> 03:45.405
They said to him, Rabbi, which means teacher, where are you staying?

03:46.147 --> 03:51.096
And then Jesus said in verse 39, the first part of that verse, come and you'll see.

03:51.557 --> 03:52.178
He replied.

03:52.418 --> 03:58.470
Now, in these verses that we just read from verses 35 to the first part of verse 39, we find two invitations.

03:58.871 --> 04:02.899
The first one there is when it says the next day John was standing with two of his disciples.

04:02.939 --> 04:06.245
We don't know who one of those disciples is.

04:06.305 --> 04:08.550
We know that one was Andrew.

04:08.610 --> 04:09.792
We'll get to that in a few moments.

04:09.933 --> 04:12.658
Probably the other one was the Apostle John.

04:12.738 --> 04:18.029
It could be that the other one was Philip because we're going to read a little bit about Philip and as part of this story in a few moments.

04:18.069 --> 04:23.800
We don't really know, but we know that two of the disciples of John the Baptist were standing there with John the Baptist.

04:23.820 --> 04:27.828
And then when John said these words, look the Lamb of God.

04:27.848 --> 04:29.431
That is the first invitation.

04:29.471 --> 04:32.818
You can circle that in your Bibles if you'd like the first invitation.

04:33.410 --> 04:41.505
that John the Baptist, who was a guy who had been called to preach the gospel, a guy who had been called to win people to Christ and to point people to Christ.

04:41.906 --> 04:44.230
And here he did what he always did.

04:44.310 --> 04:46.755
He did what was normal in his journey.

04:46.975 --> 04:49.981
He just simply said, look the Lamb of God.

04:50.722 --> 04:55.531
Now the reason that's an invitation is because what he was doing is he was telling people, look to Jesus.

04:56.252 --> 04:57.234
Look to Jesus.

04:57.602 --> 05:01.886
And just as that was John the Baptist calling, that was his passion, it was his heart.

05:02.146 --> 05:06.130
Let's make sure we understand it should be our passion as well.

05:06.751 --> 05:10.314
Because just as John the Baptist was called, so are you.

05:11.395 --> 05:17.781
Just as John the Baptist was told, it is your responsibility to win people and point people to Christ.

05:18.902 --> 05:27.410
Every one of you in this room, every person who's a follower of Christ who's in this room or watching or listening right now, we have that same calling on our lives.

05:27.746 --> 05:32.712
We have that same calling that God has extended to us to place in our lives.

05:33.052 --> 05:37.618
And we don't have a choice if we're a follower of Jesus.

05:38.399 --> 05:43.265
The words from our lips often should be, look, the Lamb of God.

05:44.086 --> 05:46.269
It's what I do when I preach on this stage.

05:46.509 --> 05:49.392
It's also what I do when I live my life Monday through Saturday.

05:50.153 --> 05:54.859
It's what you should do if you have the opportunity of leading a life group here at Thomas Road.

05:55.099 --> 05:57.202
But it's also what you should do when you go to work.

05:57.858 --> 06:05.106
It's also what you should do when you happen to go to school, or when you're hanging out in the neighborhood, certainly when you're at home.

06:05.889 --> 06:09.202
This week we had a group of 50 individuals who were down in Guatemala.

06:09.794 --> 06:17.763
an incredible team that went down and dedicated five wells that they raised the money to place in areas where they did not have clean water.

06:18.083 --> 06:28.494
Had the opportunity, a couple of the members over that trip who were doctors, had the opportunity of doing medical missions there and serving individuals in that region who were underserved.

06:29.095 --> 06:39.506
I had the opportunity of going down and spending a few days with them and during that time we dedicated a new training center where we're training individuals who will reach the young people of that nation.

06:39.746 --> 06:43.731
And all of those 50 people who were long on that trip, let me tell you what their calling was.

06:44.192 --> 06:58.050
And there were people in that group that were real estate agents, and there were people who were electricians, and there were people who owned other kinds of businesses and builders, and there were people on that trip that were, you know, retired individuals, there were all kinds of people on that trip.

06:58.331 --> 07:00.273
And they all went to do this.

07:00.313 --> 07:09.746
One thing, look, the Lamb of God, to have the opportunity of using their skills, their talents, their abilities,

07:10.114 --> 07:18.828
to literally go into a people that they don't know and to, in a way, knock on their door and just say, look, the Lamb of God.

07:19.949 --> 07:21.752
You see, that's what God has called all of us to.

07:21.972 --> 07:26.680
And that's what John did in the first part of this passage, in this first invitation, the invitation to see.

07:26.700 --> 07:27.461
Just see.

07:28.242 --> 07:30.706
Look who Jesus is.

07:31.490 --> 07:42.942
The second invitation that we see down in verse 39 is when after the individuals, when Andrew and either Philip or John followed along and walked after Jesus, they went to him.

07:43.403 --> 07:44.924
And they said, hey, where are you staying?

07:45.505 --> 07:48.929
Now, they weren't asking that so they could send him a Domino's pizza later in the night.

07:48.989 --> 07:50.630
They weren't asking him so they could drop by.

07:50.951 --> 07:54.154
They were asking him because they wanted to spend some time with him.

07:54.174 --> 07:55.496
And they knew he was busy.

07:55.596 --> 07:56.617
He's the Lamb of God.

07:56.637 --> 07:57.778
He's got a full schedule.

07:57.858 --> 08:04.729
And so they were asking the question like, we just want to be able to talk to you and inquire of you and to learn from you.

08:04.789 --> 08:06.572
Is that in that time, in that culture?

08:06.632 --> 08:08.034
That's exactly what they did.

08:08.555 --> 08:14.305
The individuals wanted to follow the teacher, follow the rabbi, to be inspired, to be encouraged, to be instructed.

08:14.886 --> 08:17.730
And then Jesus said this word in the first part of 39.

08:18.251 --> 08:20.114
He says, come and you'll see.

08:20.770 --> 08:25.035
You see, invitations are not only extended from Christ himself as it was here.

08:25.155 --> 08:26.076
Come and you'll see.

08:26.476 --> 08:28.518
The invitation was also issued by John.

08:29.139 --> 08:30.761
Look the Lamb of God.

08:31.061 --> 08:44.656
And regardless of where the invitation is coming from, regardless of where the opportunity is for people to see and experience the power of God, all of it is recognized as it points to Jesus.

08:46.518 --> 08:50.642
You see, Jesus, every single day, 24 hours a day,

08:51.138 --> 08:56.949
Seven days a week, 365 days a year and on leap year 366.

08:56.989 --> 09:02.940
He is issuing that invitation, come and see.

09:02.980 --> 09:09.052
Now why that's important for us today is that we know that there are a lot of people in our community.

09:10.094 --> 09:12.338
We're walking up and down the streets of Lynchburg.

09:13.378 --> 09:29.515
We have the opportunity of working in the various businesses, having the opportunity of going to the local schools, having the opportunity of playing ball in the local fields, having the opportunity of spending time in the local restaurants, having the opportunity of living in the neighborhoods in which we live.

09:29.876 --> 09:43.250
And here is what we must all recognize and embrace is that every single one of them is a recipient of the call of Jesus, the invitation of Jesus saying, come.

09:43.458 --> 09:43.939
and see.

09:45.121 --> 09:49.009
And it is our responsibility to help get them there.

09:50.251 --> 10:02.935
You see, in this passage, we see just in the first few verses of this passage, we see that the job of Jesus come and you'll see in our jobs, look, the Lamb of God.

10:04.097 --> 10:06.482
It's the invitation to see who Christ is.

10:06.978 --> 10:17.017
Now, the second part of this passage, we've broken it down, is not only the invitation to see, but we also go to the second part of this first passage, and that's just seeing the obvious.

10:17.598 --> 10:21.104
Like seeing the obvious, look what it says in verse 39, the rest of that verse.

10:21.425 --> 10:26.354
And so they went, after Jesus said, coming you'll see, so now they went.

10:26.498 --> 10:29.221
And they saw where he was staying, and they stayed with him that day.

10:29.602 --> 10:35.589
They spent time talking with Jesus, inquiring of Jesus, asking all kinds of questions.

10:35.609 --> 10:36.930
You can imagine what they were doing.

10:37.371 --> 10:38.652
It was about four in the afternoon.

10:39.193 --> 10:44.800
And so Andrew, Simon Peter's brother, was one of the two who heard John and followed him, verse 41.

10:46.141 --> 10:53.490
He first, talking about Andrew, he first found his own brother, Simon, and that's Simon Peter, and he told him,

10:53.602 --> 10:56.691
We have found the Messiah, which has translated the Christ.

10:57.172 --> 10:59.057
And he brought Simon to Jesus.

10:59.519 --> 11:02.668
When Jesus saw him, he said, you are Simon, son of John.

11:02.728 --> 11:05.636
You will be called Cephas, which has translated Peter.

11:05.957 --> 11:07.762
So here, if again, if you're

11:07.874 --> 11:13.519
circling in your Bibles, if you're following along here with these seven invitations, here we find the third invitation.

11:13.780 --> 11:26.532
And the third invitation comes from Andrew when it says in verse 41, he went and found his brother Simon, or Peter, and he told him we found the Messiah, and he brought Simon to Jesus.

11:27.333 --> 11:36.882
So it wasn't just simply an opportunity of someone saying, hey, look, the Lamb of God, now it's an opportunity of saying, hey, I want to take you to see the Lamb of God.

11:37.378 --> 11:40.022
I want to walk you to where Jesus is.

11:40.322 --> 11:41.964
I want to bring you along.

11:42.185 --> 11:49.635
And so it's this opportunity of not only look, it's the Lamb of God, but now it's the opportunity of like, hey, let me share with you who he is.

11:49.715 --> 11:55.423
You see what we learned from this passage is just simply this, as God has called all of us to do all of this.

11:56.384 --> 12:00.530
He's called all of us to yes, go and to knock on the doors.

12:00.866 --> 12:04.291
He's called all of us to extend the invitation to look.

12:04.311 --> 12:05.192
It's the Lamb of God.

12:05.513 --> 12:15.146
But He's also extended to us the responsibility and the calling that not only do we point people to Jesus, we bring people to Jesus this week.

12:15.166 --> 12:20.434
Kevin Foster just shared with me just this morning, just a few moments ago before I came out in the service.

12:20.674 --> 12:33.138
He shared that Jen Barrick, who many of you know, who was a young lady in our church, who 18 years ago, 19 years ago, I believe, was in an accident, a devastating accident with a traumatic brain injury.

12:33.158 --> 12:36.284
Many thought that she would not survive, that she would not live.

12:36.304 --> 12:37.667
The doctor said there was no hope.

12:37.687 --> 12:40.232
She was in a coma for 45 or so days.

12:40.833 --> 12:41.394
And then,

12:41.538 --> 12:50.357
When she couldn't talk to her family, when she couldn't talk to her friends, she couldn't be awake to have conversations with her mom and her dad who were in the accident with her.

12:50.657 --> 12:51.379
Here's what she did.

12:51.399 --> 12:58.614
The only conversations that she could have is she simply prayed and she had conversations with Jesus.

12:58.714 --> 13:00.498
And this week, Jim,

13:00.610 --> 13:06.738
19 years after that accident when people said that she would never walk again, talk again, or maybe even breathe again.

13:06.998 --> 13:07.980
Guess what she did this week?

13:08.280 --> 13:18.914
This week she had the opportunity of speaking to 1500 students in schools within the country of Guatemala and to share the gospel with them.

13:18.934 --> 13:19.955
How cool is that?

13:20.016 --> 13:27.986
Someone who has every reason to sit on the front porch in a rocking chair.

13:28.898 --> 13:34.804
to take it easy because of the continued damage of that accident all of those years ago.

13:35.444 --> 13:38.708
The struggles that she has physically because of that accident.

13:39.008 --> 13:40.169
But no, here's what she's doing.

13:40.209 --> 13:42.732
She's going and saying, look, it's the Lamb of God.

13:43.873 --> 13:44.533
Come and see.

13:44.593 --> 13:46.836
Let me take you to Him.

13:48.677 --> 13:51.860
You see, that calling is something that is on every single one of our lives.

13:51.920 --> 13:56.285
It's not only the opportunity, the invitation to see, but it's to see the obvious.

13:56.325 --> 13:57.586
And the obvious is this.

13:58.562 --> 14:03.369
is that when you have the opportunity of seeing who Jesus is, you see the miraculous.

14:04.170 --> 14:05.532
You see the supernatural.

14:07.214 --> 14:16.707
Those two disciples had the opportunity of going and sitting down and having a long day conversation with Jesus probably from about 10 o'clock in the morning till about four o'clock in the afternoon.

14:17.048 --> 14:19.170
They had that opportunity of having a conversation with Jesus.

14:19.471 --> 14:20.532
That would be fun, wouldn't it?

14:20.953 --> 14:23.617
To sit there in a room with Jesus, just three people and asking questions.

14:23.637 --> 14:24.658
That'd be a lot of fun.

14:25.282 --> 14:26.724
That's what they had the opportunity of doing.

14:27.025 --> 14:33.956
And I know this that during that time when they had the opportunity of having this conversation, what they saw was something that amazed them.

14:34.777 --> 14:41.909
Now, I know in Scripture, we see over and over again that every time anyone had the opportunity of talking with Jesus, they were overwhelmed, they were amazed.

14:42.270 --> 14:47.378
We talk about even when Jesus was a 12-year-old boy, Luke 2, he amazed those in the temple.

14:47.938 --> 15:17.490
talking about Nazareth, Luke chapter 4, and comparing him with the synagogue in Mark chapter 1, talking with the temple leaders in John chapter 7, talking to his own hometown in Matthew chapter 13, speaking with the disciples in Matthew 8, speaking before Pilate in Mark chapter 15, talking to the crowds regarding the people he had healed in Mark chapter 7, speaking again with the disciples in Mark chapter 19, all places where we see these words is that Jesus taught, and the people were amazed anytime that you encounter Jesus the Son of God.

15:17.602 --> 15:19.085
You were left astonished.

15:20.387 --> 15:22.471
And that's why the invitation is so important.

15:23.152 --> 15:33.532
There are people in this room today who are afraid to share the gospel because they're afraid of not knowing what to say, afraid of what if they ask a question that I don't know the answer to.

15:34.734 --> 15:36.658
I heard a story once that was shared

15:37.410 --> 15:44.684
that a pastor who sent some people in his church and they all went out and they knocked on doors in the community to win people to Christ.

15:45.025 --> 15:49.974
And as they were walking out, he said, I want all of you to pray right now before we go out and so just have a time of prayer.

15:50.716 --> 15:51.477
And so they did that.

15:51.537 --> 15:56.948
And then before they walked out, the pastor looked out to one of the people there and said, okay, tell me now, what did you pray for in that prayer?

15:56.988 --> 16:00.114
And that guy spoke up on us and said, praying that they're not home.

16:02.754 --> 16:06.018
because he's afraid of what might happen, afraid of what to say.

16:06.198 --> 16:16.690
You see, some of us walk in that position, in that situation, but understand this, our jobs is not to explain Jesus to people.

16:17.171 --> 16:25.020
Our jobs is to point people to Jesus because Jesus does not need our help to prove who he is.

16:26.341 --> 16:30.386
Our job is simply to say, look, the Lamb of God.

16:31.586 --> 16:43.802
You see, we see the obvious, but anytime that you encounter Christ, you encounter the supernatural, you encounter the God who is the God who is more than you could ever possibly imagine.

16:44.903 --> 16:52.994
Here we see this story about these individuals who were told by Jesus, told about Jesus by a friend, and it changed their lives.

16:53.795 --> 16:59.282
How many of you could sit here today and say, you know, there was somebody that I told about Jesus, and I meant it changed their lives.

16:59.842 --> 17:05.770
I know I have lots of stories that I've heard and I've seen of experience in people whose lives were changed.

17:06.551 --> 17:10.256
In fact, as we're sitting here today, I know this.

17:11.478 --> 17:20.289
There's this guy that's standing right back over here and I'm walking directly to him and he's freaking out right now, but this is Bruce Carey.

17:20.309 --> 17:27.379
And Bruce Carey has been running this camera or a camera like it in this church and the old church for how many years?

17:27.399 --> 17:28.420
57 years.

17:28.901 --> 17:29.682
He's been doing that.

17:30.050 --> 17:35.960
Now let me tell you why that's cool, but that's not why it's cool.

17:35.980 --> 17:44.213
The reason it's cool is because when he was a young boy, somebody knocked on his door and shared the gospel with his dad.

17:45.054 --> 17:46.076
And you know who that person was?

17:46.116 --> 17:48.600
It was my dad.

17:48.620 --> 17:54.430
And his family was changed because simply my dad went many, many years ago.

17:54.450 --> 17:57.074
He's old, many, many years ago.

17:59.330 --> 18:02.917
And he simply told this family, look, the Lamb of God.

18:04.199 --> 18:07.165
And his story, his life has been changed.

18:07.185 --> 18:09.750
His wife, his daughters, their lives have been changed.

18:09.830 --> 18:11.413
Grandkids, lives have been changed.

18:11.453 --> 18:11.714
Why?

18:12.195 --> 18:13.638
Because of the power of the gospel.

18:13.678 --> 18:14.840
It was not because of my dad.

18:14.860 --> 18:22.194
It was because my dad just simply was obedient to what God had called him to do and said, hey, look, the Lamb of God.

18:22.818 --> 18:24.940
You see, those are the stories that we need to be able to tell.

18:24.980 --> 18:27.163
Those are the stories that we need to be able to share.

18:27.203 --> 18:30.166
Those are the stories that change people's lives.

18:31.308 --> 18:33.250
And yet we don't tell them.

18:34.851 --> 18:41.879
We don't get out there and let people know who Christ is because we're afraid of, what if they ask a question that I don't know the answer to?

18:42.760 --> 18:49.087
Don't worry about that because God is God and you are not.

18:49.968 --> 18:51.410
And God's plan is always better.

18:52.194 --> 18:53.576
And so it's the invitation to see.

18:54.698 --> 18:58.284
And it's then seen the obvious of who Christ is.

18:58.544 --> 19:01.589
But the third part of this passage is this, seeing the miraculous.

19:02.090 --> 19:04.034
Look what it says in verse 5, 43.

19:04.054 --> 19:07.660
And the next day, Jesus decided to leave for Galilee.

19:08.100 --> 19:10.164
And he found Philip, and he told him, follow me.

19:10.684 --> 19:13.108
There's the fourth invitation that we see there.

19:13.169 --> 19:15.212
Jesus told him, follow me.

19:15.472 --> 19:18.898
Now, Philip was from, let's say, the hometown of Andrew and Peter.

19:19.042 --> 19:26.930
And so Philip, Dan, verse 45, Philip found Nathaniel and told him, we have found the one that Moses wrote about in the law.

19:27.250 --> 19:28.771
And so did the prophets.

19:28.791 --> 19:31.054
Jesus, the son of Joseph's from Nazareth.

19:31.334 --> 19:37.200
That's the fifth invitation when Philip told Nathaniel, we found the one that we've been looking for.

19:37.760 --> 19:40.303
We found the one that our ancestors were looking for.

19:40.383 --> 19:42.405
We have found the Messiah.

19:42.905 --> 19:44.867
Look, the Lamb of God.

19:45.888 --> 19:47.890
So Philip told us that, Daniel, that story.

19:48.418 --> 19:53.726
Then Jesus, the son of Joseph from Nazareth, 46, can anything good come out of Nazareth and Nathaniel asked him?

19:54.367 --> 19:58.053
And then here, Philip said these words, come and see.

19:58.113 --> 20:02.260
Once again, the next invitation, the sixth invitation, Philip answered.

20:02.580 --> 20:08.609
And then Jesus saw Nathaniel coming towards him and said about him, talking about Nathaniel.

20:08.990 --> 20:11.975
